  "link": "http://en.hujiang.com/new/p543464/", 
  "description": "<p>\n\t<img src=\"http://i2.w.yun.hjfile.cn/doc/201305/ca59b3e726274f518deae8f099b9af1a.jpg\" style=\"height: 338px; width: 450px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n\t《英文天天写》是沪江部落一档写作类节目，其目的在于提升大家的英语写作能力。每期节目主持人都会给出一个话题，积极参加的童鞋还会得到主持人的专业点评哦！想提高英语写作的童鞋千万不要错过哦！<a href=\"http://pass.hujiang.com/signup/?source=en_sqyd&amp;url=http://bulo.hujiang.com/menu/15011/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://i2.w.yun.hjfile.cn/doc/201304/d5e293c817a6488d819f0c13a95230e1.jpg\" style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\" /></a>去沪江部落订阅本节目！</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>背景介绍：</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tThe so-called &quot;<a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/disdain\" target=\"_blank\">disdain</a> chain&quot;（鄙视链） works like this: British drama fans look down on folks who prefer US shows, and they in turn look down on Korean soap fans. The lowest of the low in the disdain chain are fans of domestic or Thai dramas. Besides the disdain chain among drama fans, there are many other chains alike in our society.<br />\n\t电视剧鄙视链<br />\n\t英剧&gt;美剧&gt;日剧&gt;韩剧&gt;港剧&gt;台剧&gt;内地剧&gt;泰剧<br />\n\t游戏鄙视链<br />\n\t主机单机&gt;国外PC单机&gt;国外网游&gt;国内网游&gt;网页游戏、QQ游戏<br />\n\t微博鄙视链<br />\n\ttwitter/饭否&gt;新浪微博&gt;腾讯微博&gt;搜狐微博等其他微博<br />\n\t电影鄙视链<br />\n\t冷门国家文艺片&gt;欧洲文艺片&gt;日韩台小清新片&gt;老港片&gt;好莱坞大片&gt;内地片<br />\n\t音乐鄙视链<br />\n\t英伦摇滚、国内地下厂牌&gt;欧美流行音乐&gt;日韩港台流行音乐&gt;内地网络歌曲<br />\n\t动漫鄙视链<br />\n\t日韩动漫&gt;欧美动漫&gt;港台动漫&gt;内地动漫<br />\n\t论坛鄙视链<br />\n\t豆瓣&gt;天涯&gt;猫扑&gt;贴吧<br />\n\t聊天工具鄙视链<br />\n\tGtalk&gt;MSN&gt;QQ&gt;飞信<br />\n\t邮件鄙视链<br />\n\tgmail&gt; 163 mail&gt; QQmail<br />\n\t杂志鄙视链<br />\n\t《时代周刊》、《纽约客》&gt;《万象》、《天南》&gt;《新周刊》、《城市画报》&gt;《读者》&gt;《故事会》、《知音》<br />\n\t浏览器鄙视链<br />\n\t谷歌Chrome、Firefox&gt;苹果Safari、Opera&gt;遨游&gt; IE系列&gt; 360等国产山寨货<br />\n\t社交网站鄙视链<br />\n\t脸书&gt;开心网&gt;人人网&gt;腾讯朋友<br />\n\t学科鄙视链<br />\n\t工科生&gt;理科生&gt;文科生(经济法律&gt;外语&gt;文史哲)&gt;体育生艺术生<br />\n\t电视台鄙视链<br />\n\tBBC&gt;凤凰卫视&gt;CCTV&gt;湖南卫视<br />\n\t搜索引擎鄙视链<br />\n\t谷歌&gt; 百度&gt; BING/搜搜/搜狗&gt; 人民<br />\n\t&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>话题：</strong></p>\n<p>\n\t1 What do you think of this disdain chain? Does it apply to you or do you have the same psychology？</p>\n<p>\n\tOR 2 Why does this phenomenon arise in your mind?</p>\n<p>\n\tOR 3 What's the social influence of this kind of chain? Does it have adverse impact?</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>范例1：</strong></p>\n<p>\n\t&ldquo;Disdain chain&rdquo; is this kind of phenomenon that one looks down upon others while having <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/overconfidence\" target=\"_blank\">overconfidence</a> in himself, which arises in the network society and can be commonly found there. Ridiculous as it is, there is no denying that everyone may be involved in these chains. The causes are complicated, especially when they refer to <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/psychology\" target=\"_blank\">psychology</a>.<br />\n\tFirst, this phenomenon can be regarded as self-protection. People long to gain superiority complex by disdaining others and this way enables them to get feelings of self-worth at the same time. Feeling more outstanding, therefore, they can eliminate the uneasiness and get a strong sense of belonging when they join their &ldquo;class&rdquo; in disdaining the &ldquo;lower classes&rdquo;.<br />\n\tSecond, this may be a reflection of inequality in real world. Having an urgent desire to claim their own rights and dignity, netizens are obliged to pass the psychological unbalance on to the disdain chains. When disdain becomes so blatant（公然的） and people would not scruple（顾忌） to despise（鄙视） others, a new &ldquo;<a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/hierarchy\" target=\"_blank\">hierarchy</a>&rdquo;（等级制度） forms. These man-made &ldquo;classes&rdquo; divide people and even breed（导致） &ldquo;class conflicts&rdquo; in a way. You can find many examples on the Internet.<br />\n\tI don&rsquo;t think one has the right to disdain others just for the things they like. Moreover, neither individuality nor superiority will be really obtained in the disdain chain.</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>范例2：</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tIt&rsquo;s very <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/natural\" target=\"_blank\">natural</a> for people to feel superior to others. The sense of superiority sometimes hurts but also sometimes stimulates the inferior to work better. For the &ldquo;Major disdain chain&rdquo;, it does hurt. When I was in high school, those majoring in arts are mostly forced to choose so because they cannot do well in science. Arts students are often disdained by science students who think they are much more clever. Sadly, this situation is also commonly seen on college campus. Meanwhile, the sense of superiority of others can also be an impetus for the inferior. There is a reason in forming the chains like &ldquo;Browser disdain chain &rdquo;, &ldquo;Social network disdain&rdquo;, etc. Those ranking first have the capital to disdain because they are actually doing better than others to some degree. Only by comparison can one see his defects and be motivated to change.</p>\n<p>\n\t想要得到主持人专业的点评和意见吗？<a href=\"http://bulo.hujiang.com/menu/15011/item/793518/\" target=\"_blank\">快来节目现场一试身手吧&gt;&gt;</a></p>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p543464/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p543464\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a></center><h3 style=\"margin: 10px;\">本周最热文章</h3><ul style=\"margin: 5px 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p543812/\">纽约地铁温情一幕：让他靠着我睡会吧</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p543801/\">11.11又来了：光棍们悲剧大盘点</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p543538/\">又萌又有爱：7封小朋友写的情书</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.c